Install Tensorflow with no GPU support (personal use)
See tensorflow.org/versions/r0.7/get_started/os_setup.html for details

1. Make sure you have pip3
	sudo apt-get install python3-pip python3-dev

2. Install Tensorflow (CPU-only)
	sudo pip3 install --upgrade https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/linux/cpu/tensorflow-0.7.1-cp34-none-linux_x86_64.whl

3. (Optionally) Enable GPU support (see webpage)

4. Test the system 
	Open python3 
		import tensorflow as tf
		... (see webpage)
	From terminal
		python3 /usr/local/lib/python3.4/dist-packages/tensorflow/models/image/mnist/convolutional.py
	


